item.dc:creator: @tuptup13 tuptup13
item.description:
@tuptup13 wrote:

Go to your program files and look for your java folder… If its jre and not jdk you have to download it at
https://sdlc2a.sun.com/ECom/EComActionServlet;jsessionid=65FDDB1DCDE34B31657C7038649718C0

Then create a new variable named CLASSPATH on the top box in enviromental variables and as the other variable put

C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_5\bin\javac.exe
